result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
1:18 PM Defendant Jetstone A Redstart appeared by video in custody from DCJ.  Prosecuting attorney Megan E. Kelly in court for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Shelly Tomtschik appears by Zoom. 
22CF334, 22CM305, 22FO857, 22FO858
Court - notes these are Branch 1 cases. 
Atty Tomtschik - Atty Sartorius intends to raise competency in all cases. Asks that DE be put on a signature bond. Will be moving to Lacrosse.
State - asks for signature bonds. DE needs to update his address with the Court.
Court - orders $500 sign bond in 22CF334, 22CM305.
State - speaks of competency. Asks court to order competency evaluation.
Court - orders competency evaluation in 22CF334, 22CM305, 22CM227. Sets competency hearing in Branch 3 for all cases. Removes status conference on 11/7/22 from Branch 1 calendar.
Competency hearing scheduled for December 8, 2022 at 01:45 pm.

11:52 AM Defendant Jetstone A Redstart not in court.  Attorney Travis Satorius in court for Jetstone A Redstart.  Prosecuting attorney Lucas D Arras in court for the State of Wisconsin. B. Bahr - Clerk 
Atty Satorius - updates Court with information on client. Working on housing for client. Raised competency but does not see that the record reflects this. Has cases pending in Branch 1.
Court - would like all cases to track together. Set status in all cases in Branch 1 on November 7th at 3:30 PM.
Status conference scheduled for November 7, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

2:13 PM Defendant Jetstone A Redstart not in court.  Prosecuting attorney Andrew John Maki in court for the State of Wisconsin. B. Bahr - Clerk 
22CF334, 22CM305, 22FO857, 22FO858
Court - has reviewed complaint. Finds probable cause for arrest in 22CF334. Bond hearing was to take place yesterday, 9/22/22. DE was not able to appear - was transferred to another facility.
Initial appearance on September 23, 2022 at 02:00 pm.
